Why are we looking for MP and not .*, like we do with the baseboard?
Two features requires same json file for configuration. If any one patch is merged and the other one can be rebased on top of master.
Please open one patch.  If you need to stack one on top of another, feel free.

Rebased the below patch to this gerrit patch.
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/48005
@Ed - This has been ready to go for a while now.
One remaining question.  It's not clear how this could've worked as-written, then yes, it should be good to go.

Also, the IPMB device patches haven't been merged yet, which this would require.  If the authors wanted to, they could split up the board itself from the IpmbDevice instance, and this specifically could go in faster.

Split the patch and submitted a new patch for board in gerrit.
https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/58408
Where is this variable coming from?  this would normally be $Index.

This variable is coming from IPMB FRU property. This implementation is under review in gerrit. IPMBINDEX will provide the bus number for each IPMB device.

https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/entity-manager/+/57534/7/src/fru_utils.cpp#1302
